 second step of the grammaticalization chain is then the change from a resultative reading entailing stative to a pure stative reading. This is likely to have been pioneered by predicates of profession, which are still one of the most frequent predicates f
ound with the copula in Sri Lanka Malay. Only later would other predicates where a resultative meaning is impossible (e.g. sex) have followed suit. The proposed development can then be summarized as follows:}
